SQL_Statement: SELECT  SUM(cnt) FROM ( SELECT  z, COUNT(DISTINCT x) AS cnt FROM ( SELECT a.follower AS x ,  b.followee AS z FROM  [354].[twitter_rv.6157841] a JOIN  [354].[twitter_rv.6157841] b ON a.followee = b.follower ) joined WHERE  z < 4000 GROUP BY  z --OPTION (MERGE JOIN ,  ORDER GROUP) ) joined_distinct
Equivalent_Queries:
SELECT SUM(COUNT(DISTINCT a.follower)) AS Total_Distinct_Followers
FROM [354].[twitter_rv.6157841] a
JOIN [354].[twitter_rv.6157841] b ON a.followee = b.follower
WHERE b.followee < 4000
GROUP BY b.followee;

SQL_Statement: SELECT  ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY TAIL_NUM ORDER BY  YEAR,  MONTH,  DAY_OF_MONTH,  ARR_TIME) ID,  ORIGIN,  DEST,  TAIL_NUM,  FL_NUM, DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR,  MONTH,  DAY_OF_MONTH) DATE, CARRIER,  DEP_TIME,  ARR_TIME,  DISTANCE,  AIR_TIME FROM  [372].[flights09] WHERE  TAIL_NUM != ''
Equivalent_Queries:
SELECT ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY TAIL_NUM ORDER BY YEAR, MONTH, DAY_OF_MONTH, ARR_TIME) AS ID,
       sub.ORIGIN, 
       sub.DEST, 
       sub.TAIL_NUM, 
       sub.FL_NUM, 
       DATEFROMPARTS(sub.YEAR, sub.MONTH, sub.DAY_OF_MONTH) AS DATE, 
       sub.CARRIER, 
       sub.DEP_TIME, 
       sub.ARR_TIME, 
       sub.DISTANCE, 
       sub.AIR_TIME
FROM (
    SELECT *
    FROM [372].[flights09]
    WHERE TAIL_NUM != ''
) AS sub;

SQL_Statement: SELECT  [All Proteins], SUM (numuniquepepsCG242_01+numuniquepepsCG242_02+numuniquepepsCG242_03) AS [CG242 unique peps sum] FROM  [412].[Oyster 242 spec counts] GROUP BY  [All Proteins]
Equivalent_Queries:
SELECT [All Proteins], SUM(numuniquepepsCG242_01 + numuniquepepsCG242_02 + numuniquepepsCG242_03) AS [CG242 unique peps sum]
FROM [412].[Oyster 242 spec counts] AS counts
WHERE EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM [412].[Oyster 242 spec counts] AS valid
    WHERE valid.[All Proteins] = counts.[All Proteins]
)
GROUP BY [All Proteins];

SQL_Statement: select distinct a.fullname,  p.id as pubID from field f,  author a,  publication p where f.p='author' and f.k=p.id and f.v=a.fullname
Equivalent_Queries:
SELECT DISTINCT 
    a.fullname, 
    p.id AS pubID
FROM 
    field f
INNER JOIN 
    publication p 
    ON f.k = p.id
INNER JOIN 
    author a 
    ON f.v = a.fullname
WHERE 
    f.p = 'author';

SQL_Statement: SELECT  Count (*) From ( SELECT * FROM  [1123].[BiGo_mito_cleam] where context like '__CT_' --modified respectively for CA,  CT,  CC and CT_Count >= 5 and ratio > 0) --modified respectively for zero methylation (= 0.000 ) betty
Equivalent_Queries:
WITH FilteredData AS (
    -- The original inner query becomes the outer query in the CTE.
    SELECT *
    FROM [1123].[BiGo_mito_cleam]
    WHERE context LIKE '__CT_'
      AND CT_Count >= 5
      AND ratio > 0
)
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM (
    -- The count operation becomes the inner query using the CTE.
    SELECT *
    FROM FilteredData
) AS InnerQuery

SQL_Statement: select category from ( SELECT  case when budget = 'Moore' then 'Moore/Sloan' when budget = 'Sloan' then 'Moore/Sloan' else budget end as budget ,  case when Description Like '%Faculty:%' and category_label = 'Salaries' then 'Faculty' when Description Like '%Faculty:%' and category_label = 'Benefits' then 'Faculty' when Description Like '%tudents%' and category_label = 'Salaries' then 'Students' when Description Like '%tudents%' and category_label = 'Benefits' then 'Students' when Description Like '%ost-doc%' and category_label = 'Benefits' then 'Postdoc' when Description Like '%ost-doc%' and category_label = 'Salaries' then 'Postdoc' when Description Like '%Pro Staff%' and category_label = 'Salaries' then 'Research Staff' when Description Like '%Pro Staff%' and category_label = 'Benefits' then 'Research Staff' when Description Like '%Admin Pro%' and category_label = 'Salaries' then 'Admin Staff' when Description Like '%Admin Pro%' and category_label = 'Benefits' then 'Admin Staff' when Description Like '%Classified Staff%' and category_label = 'Salaries' then 'Admin Staff' when Description Like '%Classified Staff%' and category_label = 'Benefits' then 'Admin Staff' when Description Like '%Bill%' and category_label = 'Salaries' then 'Admin Staff' when Description Like '%Bill%' and category_label = 'Benefits' then 'Admin Staff' when Description Like '%visiting%' and category_label = 'Salaries' then 'Admin Staff' when Description Like '%visiting%' and category_label = 'Benefits' then 'Admin Staff' when Description Like '%Chance%' and category_label = 'Salaries' then 'Admin Staff' when Description Like '%Chance%' and category_label = 'Benefits' then 'Admin Staff' when Description Like '%Hyak%' and category_label = 'Salaries' then 'Admin Staff' when Description Like '%Hyak%' and category_label = 'Benefits' then 'Admin Staff' when Description Like '%Hourly%' and category_label = 'Salaries' then 'Admin Staff' when Description Like '%Hourly%' and category_label = 'Benefits' then 'Admin Staff' when category_label = 'Consulting' or category_label = 'Equipment' or category_label = 'Supplies' or category_label = 'Contractual Services' or category_label='Recharge' then 'Other' else category_label end as category ,  Description ,  case when len(INV_Date) <2 then NULL when PO_Invoice = 'CR3566' then '9/1/2015' else cast(inv_date as date) end as inv_date ,  cast(case when BAR_Amt is null then Encumbered else BAR_Amt end as float) as amount ,  cd,  PO_Invoice,  Encumbered FROM  [1314howe].[ALL_Operations_Details.csv] ) x group by category
Equivalent_Queries:
SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN budget = 'Moore' THEN 'Moore/Sloan' 
        WHEN budget = 'Sloan' THEN 'Moore/Sloan' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Faculty:%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Faculty' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Faculty:%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Faculty' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%tudents%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Students' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%tudents%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Students' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%ost-doc%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Postdoc' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%ost-doc%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Postdoc' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Pro Staff%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Research Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Pro Staff%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Research Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Admin Pro%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Admin Pro%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Classified Staff%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Classified Staff%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Bill%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Bill%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%visiting%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%visiting%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Chance%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Chance%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Hyak%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Hyak%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Hourly%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Hourly%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN category_label IN ('Consulting', 'Equipment', 'Supplies', 'Contractual Services', 'Recharge') THEN 'Other' 
        ELSE category_label 
    END AS category
FROM 
    [1314howe].[ALL_Operations_Details.csv]
GROUP BY 
    CASE 
        WHEN budget = 'Moore' THEN 'Moore/Sloan' 
        WHEN budget = 'Sloan' THEN 'Moore/Sloan' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Faculty:%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Faculty' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Faculty:%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Faculty' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%tudents%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Students' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%tudents%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Students' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%ost-doc%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Postdoc' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%ost-doc%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Postdoc' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Pro Staff%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Research Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Pro Staff%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Research Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Admin Pro%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Admin Pro%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Classified Staff%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Classified Staff%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Bill%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Bill%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%visiting%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%visiting%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Chance%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Chance%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Hyak%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Hyak%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Hourly%' AND category_label = 'Salaries' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN Description LIKE '%Hourly%' AND category_label = 'Benefits' THEN 'Admin Staff' 
        WHEN category_label IN ('Consulting', 'Equipment', 'Supplies', 'Contractual Services', 'Recharge') THEN 'Other' 
        ELSE category_label 
    END

SQL_Statement: WITH  Radius AS (SELECT  6378100 AS Radius) ,  Numbered AS (SELECT  [DateTime],  [LAT],  [LON],  ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY  [DateTime] ASC) AS [Row] FROM  [1059].[SDS_VIEW]) SELECT  b.[DateTime] ,  Radius * (SQRT(POWER(b.[LAT]-a.[LAT], 2) + POWER(b.[LON]-a.[LON], 2))) / 360 * 2 * 3.1415926 * Radius AS Euclid FROM  Numbered a ,  Numbered b ,  Radius WHERE  a.[Row] + 1 = b.[Row] ORDER BY  [DateTime] DESC
Equivalent_Queries:
WITH Radius AS (
    SELECT 6378100 AS Radius
),
Numbered AS (
    SELECT [DateTime], [LAT], [LON], 
           ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY [DateTime] ASC) AS [Row]
    FROM [1059].[SDS_VIEW]
)
SELECT 
    b.[DateTime],
    r.Radius * (SQRT(POWER(b.[LAT] - a.[LAT], 2) + POWER(b.[LON] - a.[LON], 2))) / 360 * 2 * 3.1415926 * r.Radius AS Euclid
FROM 
    Numbered a
JOIN 
    Numbered b ON a.[Row] + 1 = b.[Row]
JOIN
    Radius r
ORDER BY 
    b.[DateTime] DESC;

SQL_Statement: SELECT  DISTINCT CASE WHEN PATINDEX('%[0-9]%',  [protein]) = 1 -- first char is number AND  CHARINDEX(', ',  [protein]) = 0 -- AND  no comma present THEN [protein] ELSE SUBSTRING([protein], PATINDEX('%[0-9]%',  [protein]),  -- start at first number CHARINDEX(', ',  [protein])-PATINDEX('%[0-9]%',  [protein])) -- length END AS [protein D2] ,  [tot indep spectra] AS [tot spectra D2] FROM  [412].[D2_trip_files_169_170_171.prot.txt]
Equivalent_Queries:
SELECT DISTINCT
    subquery.[protein D2],
    subquery.[tot spectra D2]
FROM (
    SELECT
        CASE 
            WHEN PATINDEX('%[0-9]%', [protein]) = 1 AND CHARINDEX(', ', [protein]) = 0 THEN [protein]
            ELSE SUBSTRING([protein], PATINDEX('%[0-9]%', [protein]), CHARINDEX(', ', [protein]) - PATINDEX('%[0-9]%', [protein]))
        END AS [protein D2],
        [tot indep spectra] AS [tot spectra D2]
    FROM [412].[D2_trip_files_169_170_171.prot.txt]
) AS subquery

SELECT  * FROM  ( SELECT  sql_query,  sql_query_hash ,  x_col_name,  y_col_name ,  vizlet_type ,  row_number() over (partition by sql_query,  sql_query_hash,  x_col_name,  y_col_name order by score desc) as rnk FROM  [1314howe].[Vizlet Scores] --GROUP BY  sql_query,  sql_query_hash,  x_col_name,  y_col_name ) x WHERE  x.rnk = 1
Equivalent_Queries:
WITH RankedVizlets AS (
    SELECT
        sql_query,
        sql_query_hash,
        x_col_name,
        y_col_name,
        vizlet_type,
        score,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY sql_query, sql_query_hash, x_col_name, y_col_name
            ORDER BY score DESC
        ) AS rnk
    FROM [1314howe].[Vizlet Scores]
)
SELECT 
    sql_query,
    sql_query_hash,
    x_col_name,
    y_col_name,
    vizlet_type,
    score

SQL_Statement: SELECT  c.DEST,  n.ORIGIN,  c.ARR_TIME,  n.DEP_TIME FROM  [372].[flights09_part] c JOIN [372].[flights09_part] n ON c.TAIL_NUM = n.TAIL_NUM AND  (c.DATE < n.DATE OR  (c.DATE = n.DATE AND  c.ARR_TIME <= n.DEP_TIME)) AND  c.DEST != n.ORIGIN
Equivalent_Queries:
SELECT  
    c.DEST,  
    n.ORIGIN,  
    c.ARR_TIME,  
    n.DEP_TIME 
FROM 
    [372].[flights09_part] c 
JOIN 
    [372].[flights09_part] n 
ON 
    c.TAIL_NUM = n.TAIL_NUM 
    AND (
        CASE 
            WHEN c.DATE < n.DATE THEN 1
            WHEN c.DATE = n.DATE AND c.ARR_TIME <= n.DEP_TIME THEN 1
            ELSE 0
        END = 1
    )
    AND c.DEST != n.ORIGIN;

SQL_Statement: SELECT  count(*) FROM  ( SELECT  fs.sql_query,  vs.query_hash,  vs.x_col,  vs.y_col,  vs.vizlet_type,  count(*) as score FROM  [1307].[vizlets_28nov11_16h16m43s_every_displayed_vizlet.csv] vs LEFT OUTER JOIN  [1307].[vizlets_23nov11_10h34m16s_vizlet_and_action_features.csv] fs ON (vs.query_hash = fs.sql_query_hash and vs.x_col = fs.x_col_name and vs.y_col = fs.y_col_name and vs.vizlet_type = fs.vizlet_type) WHERE   1=1 GROUP BY  fs.sql_query,  vs.query_hash,  vs.x_col,  vs.y_col,  vs.vizlet_type --ORDER BY  count(*) desc --  ) z
Equivalent_Queries:
WITH VizletCounts AS (
    SELECT
        fs.sql_query,
        vs.query_hash,
        vs.x_col,
        vs.y_col,
        vs.vizlet_type,
        COUNT(*) AS score
    FROM
        [1307].[vizlets_28nov11_16h16m43s_every_displayed_vizlet.csv] vs
    LEFT JOIN
        [1307].[vizlets_23nov11_10h34m16s_vizlet_and_action_features.csv] fs
        ON vs.query_hash = fs.sql_query_hash
        AND vs.x_col = fs.x_col_name
        AND vs.y_col = fs.y_col_name
        AND vs.vizlet_type = fs.vizlet_type
    GROUP BY
        fs.sql_query,
        vs.query_hash,
        vs.x_col,
        vs.y_col,
        vs.vizlet_type
)
SELECT
    COUNT(*)
FROM
    VizletCounts;

SQL_Statement: SELECT  M1ID, M1ratio, T1D3ratio, T1D5ratio FROM  [1123].[filt3_M1]m1 join [1123].[filt3_M3]m3 on m1.M1ID=m3.M3ID join [1123].[filt3_T1D3]t1d3 on m1.M1ID=t1d3.T1D3ID join [1123].[filt3_T1D5]t1d5 on m1.M1ID=t1d5.T1D5ID join [1123].[filt3_T3D3]t3d3 on m1.M1ID=t3d3.T3D3ID join [1123].[filt3_T3D5]t3d5 on m1.M1ID=t3d5.T3D5ID where [M1coverage] >= '5' and [M3coverage] >= '5' and [T1D3coverage] >= '5' and [T1D5coverage] >= '5' and [T3D3coverage] >= '5' and [T3D5coverage] >= '5'
Equivalent_Queries:
SELECT 
    M1ID, 
    M1ratio, 
    T1D3ratio, 
    T1D5ratio 
FROM 
    (
        SELECT 
            m1.M1ID, 
            m1.M1ratio, 
            t1d3.T1D3ratio, 
            t1d5.T1D5ratio,
            m3.M3coverage, 
            t1d3.T1D3coverage, 
            t1d5.T1D5coverage,
            t3d3.T3D3coverage,
            t3d5.T3D5coverage
        FROM 
            [1123].[filt3_M1] m1 
        JOIN 
            [1123].[filt3_M3] m3 ON m1.M1ID = m3.M3ID 
        JOIN 
            [1123].[filt3_T1D3] t1d3 ON m1.M1ID = t1d3.T1D3ID 
        JOIN 
            [1123].[filt3_T1D5] t1d5 ON m1.M1ID = t1d5.T1D5ID 
        JOIN 
            [1123].[filt3_T3D3] t3d3 ON m1.M1ID = t3d3.T3D3ID 
        JOIN 
            [1123].[filt3_T3D5] t3d5 ON m1.M1ID = t3d5.T3D5ID
    ) subquery
WHERE 
    subquery.M3coverage >= '5' 
    AND subquery.T1D3coverage >= '5' 
    AND subquery.T1D5coverage >= '5' 
    AND subquery.T3D3coverage >= '5' 
    AND subquery.T3D5coverage >= '5'

SQL_Statement: SELECT DISTINCT T.day as Day,  T.[file] as File_Id, (CAST(T.opp as FLOAT))/(CAST(T.evt as FLOAT)) as opp_evt, (1000*(-9*POWER(10, -5)*POWER(CAST(D.[STREAM.PRESSURE] as FLOAT), 4) + 0.0066 * POWER(CAST(D.[STREAM.PRESSURE] as FLOAT), 3) - 0.173 * POWER(CAST(D.[STREAM.PRESSURE] as FLOAT), 2) + 2.5013 * CAST(D.[STREAM.PRESSURE] as FLOAT) + 2.1059) * 0.1738) as flow_rate FROM  [1057].[Thompson9_stats.tab] as T, [1057].[Thompson9_sds.tab] as D WHERE  T.day = D.day AND  T.[file] = D.[file] AND  ISNUMERIC(D.[STREAM.PRESSURE])<>0
Equivalent_Queries:
SELECT DISTINCT 
    T.day AS Day, 
    T.[file] AS File_Id, 
    (CAST(T.opp AS FLOAT)) / (CAST(T.evt AS FLOAT)) AS opp_evt, 
    (1000 * (-9 * POWER(10, -5) * POWER(CAST(D.[STREAM.PRESSURE] AS FLOAT), 4) 
        + 0.0066 * POWER(CAST(D.[STREAM.PRESSURE] AS FLOAT), 3) 
        - 0.173 * POWER(CAST(D.[STREAM.PRESSURE] AS FLOAT), 2) 
        + 2.5013 * CAST(D.[STREAM.PRESSURE] AS FLOAT) 
        + 2.1059) * 0.1738) AS flow_rate 
FROM  
    [1057].[Thompson9_stats.tab] AS T
INNER JOIN 
    [1057].[Thompson9_sds.tab] AS D 
ON 
    T.day = D.day AND T.[file] = D.[file]
WHERE  
    ISNUMERIC(D.[STREAM.PRESSURE]) <> 0;

SQL_Statement: SELECT isnull(a.row_num, isnull(b.row_num, null) ) as row , isnull(a.column_num, isnull(b.column_num, null) ) as row , a.row_num, a.column_num, b.row_num, b.column_num  ,  a.value ,  b.value, a.value + b.value sum_value FROM [187].[table_Matrix A.txt]  A full outer join [187].[table_Matrix B.txt] B on A.row_num = B.row_num and A.column_num  = b.column_num
Equivalent_Queries:
SELECT 
    isnull(a.row_num, isnull(b.row_num, null)) as row,
    isnull(a.column_num, isnull(b.column_num, null)) as column,
    a.row_num, 
    a.column_num, 
    b.row_num, 
    b.column_num, 
    a.value, 
    b.value, 
    a.value + b.value as sum_value
FROM 
    [187].[table_Matrix A.txt] A
FULL OUTER JOIN 
    [187].[table_Matrix B.txt] B
    ON A.row_num = B.row_num AND A.column_num = B.column_num
WHERE
    EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM [187].[table_Matrix B.txt] B2 WHERE B2.row_num = A.row_num AND B2.column_num = A.column_num)
    OR EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM [187].[table_Matrix A.txt] A2 WHERE A2.row_num = B.row_num AND A2.column_num = B.column_num);

SELECT 
    MAX(salary) AS max_salary, 
    MIN(salary) AS min_salary, 
    AVG(salary) AS avg_salary, 
    COUNT(*) AS total_entries
FROM (
    SELECT 
        Name, 
        [Job Title] AS job_title, 
        [2010 Gross Earnings] AS salary 
    FROM [1314howe].[uw_salaries_2011.txt]
) x 
WHERE 
    (job_title LIKE '%RESEAR%PRINCI%' OR job_title LIKE 'ASSISTANT PROFESSOR')
    AND name LIKE '%balazinska%' 
    AND job_title NOT LIKE '%APL%' 
    AND salary < 112800;

SQL_Statement: SELECT term_id, tf, D, docs_with_T , log(D)-log(docs_with_T) as idf , tf * (log(D)-log(docs_with_T)) as [tf-idf] FROM ( SELECT term_id, SUM(frequency) as tf , (SELECT  COUNT(distinct doc_id) FROM  [1314howe].[reuters_terms.csv]) as D , COUNT(*) as docs_with_T FROM  [1314howe].[reuters_terms.csv] GROUP BY  term_id ) a ORDER BY  [tf-idf] desc
Equivalent_Queries:
WITH TermStats AS (
    SELECT 
        term_id, 
        SUM(frequency) AS tf, 
        (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT doc_id) FROM [1314howe].[reuters_terms.csv]) AS D, 
        COUNT(*) AS docs_with_T 
    FROM 
        [1314howe].[reuters_terms.csv] 
    GROUP BY 
        term_id
)
SELECT 
    term_id, 
    tf, 
    D, 
    docs_with_T, 
    LOG(D) - LOG(docs_with_T) AS idf, 
    tf * (LOG(D) - LOG(docs_with_T)) AS [tf-idf] 
FROM 
    TermStats 
ORDER BY 
    [tf-idf] DESC;

SQL_Statement: WITH  Numbered AS (SELECT  [DateTime],  [LAT],  [LON],  ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY  [DateTime] ASC) AS [Row] FROM  [1059].[SDS_VIEW]) ,  Paired AS (SELECT  a.[DateTime] AS [DateTime] ,  DATEDIFF(second,  a.[DateTime],  b.[DateTime]) AS [Elapsed (s)] ,  a.[LAT] AS [lat1deg] ,  a.[LON] AS [lon1deg] ,  b.[LAT] AS [lat2deg] ,  b.[LON] AS [lon2deg] ,  a.[LAT] * PI() / 180 AS [lat1] ,  b.[LAT] * PI() / 180  AS [lat2] ,  (a.[LAT] - b.[LAT]) * PI() / 180 AS [dlat] ,  (a.[LON] - b.[LON]) * PI() / 180 AS [dlon] FROM  Numbered a JOIN  Numbered b ON a.[Row]+1 = b.[Row]) ,  Trig AS (SELECT  * ,  POWER(SIN(dlat/2), 2) + POWER(SIN(dlon/2), 2) * COS(lat1) * COS(lat2) AS val FROM  Paired) ,  Distance AS (SELECT  * ,  6378100 * 2 * atn2(sqrt(val),  sqrt(1-val)) AS [Distance (m)] FROM  Trig) SELECT  TOP 500 * ,  [Distance (m)] / NULLIF([Elapsed (s)], 0) AS [Velocity (m/s)] FROM  Distance
Equivalent_Queries:
SELECT TOP 500
    *,
    [Distance (m)] / NULLIF([Elapsed (s)], 0) AS [Velocity (m/s)]
FROM (
    SELECT 
        *,
        6378100 * 2 * ATN2(SQRT(val), SQRT(1-val)) AS [Distance (m)]
    FROM (
        SELECT 
            *,
            POWER(SIN(dlat / 2), 2) + POWER(SIN(dlon / 2), 2) * COS(lat1) * COS(lat2) AS val
        FROM (
            SELECT 
                a.[DateTime] AS [DateTime],
                DATEDIFF(second, a.[DateTime], b.[DateTime]) AS [Elapsed (s)],
                a.[LAT] AS [lat1deg],
                a.[LON] AS [lon1deg],
                b.[LAT] AS [lat2deg],
                b.[LON] AS [lon2deg],
                a.[LAT] * PI() / 180 AS [lat1],
                b.[LAT] * PI() / 180 AS [lat2],
                (a.[LAT] - b.[LAT]) * PI() / 180 AS [dlat],
                (a.[LON] - b.[LON]) * PI() / 180 AS [dlon]
            FROM (
                SELECT [DateTime], [LAT], [LON], ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY [DateTime] ASC) AS [Row]
                FROM [1059].[SDS_VIEW]
            ) a
            JOIN (
                SELECT [DateTime], [LAT], [LON], ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY [DateTime] ASC) AS [Row]
                FROM [1059].[SDS_VIEW]
            ) b ON a.[Row] + 1 = b.[Row]
        ) Paired
    ) Trig
) Distance;

select * FROM  ( select cast(month + '/' + day + '/' + year as datetime) as ddate ,  cast(substring(stime, 1, 2) as integer) as hours ,  cast(substring(stime, 3, 2) as integer) as minutes ,  cast(substring(stime, 5, 2) as integer) as seconds ,  * from ( select substring(sdate, len(sdate) - 5, 2) as day ,  substring(sdate, len(sdate) - 3, 2) as month ,  substring(sdate, len(sdate) - 1, 2) as year ,  substring(ztime, len(ztime) - 5, 6) as stime ,  * from ( select '00000' + cast(time as varchar) as ztime ,  '0' + cast(date as varchar) as sdate ,  * from [1002].[Tokyo_0_merged_data.csv] ) x ) y ) z order by timestamp
Equivalent_Queries:
WITH DateTransform AS (
    SELECT
        '0' + CAST(date AS VARCHAR) AS sdate,  -- Prepend '0' to date
        '00000' + CAST(time AS VARCHAR) AS ztime,  -- Prepend '00000' to time
        *
    FROM [1002].[Tokyo_0_merged_data.csv]
),
TimeComponents AS (
    SELECT
        SUBSTRING(sdate, LEN(sdate) - 5, 2) AS day,
        SUBSTRING(sdate, LEN(sdate) - 3, 2) AS month,
        SUBSTRING(sdate, LEN(sdate) - 1, 2) AS year,
        SUBSTRING(ztime, LEN(ztime) - 5, 6) AS stime,
        *
    FROM DateTransform
),
FinalTransformation AS (
    SELECT
        CAST(month + '/' + day + '/' + year AS DATETIME) AS ddate,
        CAST(SUBSTRING(stime, 1, 2) AS INTEGER) AS hours,
        CAST(SUBSTRING(stime, 3, 2) AS INTEGER) AS minutes,
        CAST(SUBSTRING(stime, 5, 2) AS INTEGER) AS seconds,
        *
    FROM TimeComponents
)
SELECT *
FROM FinalTransformation
ORDER BY timestamp;

SQL_Statement: WITH  UniquePos AS (SELECT  DISTINCT [time],  [LAT],  [LON] FROM  [1059].[STATS_VIEW]), Numbered AS (SELECT  [time] as [DateTime],  [LAT],  [LON],  ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY  [Time] ASC) AS [Row] FROM  UniquePos) ,  Paired AS (SELECT  a.[DateTime] AS [DateTime] ,  DATEDIFF(second,  a.[DateTime],  b.[DateTime]) AS [Elapsed (s)] ,  a.[LAT] AS [lat1deg] ,  a.[LON] AS [lon1deg] ,  b.[LAT] AS [lat2deg] ,  b.[LON] AS [lon2deg] ,  a.[LAT] * PI() / 180 AS [lat1] ,  b.[LAT] * PI() / 180  AS [lat2] ,  (a.[LAT] - b.[LAT]) * PI() / 180 AS [dlat] ,  (a.[LON] - b.[LON]) * PI() / 180 AS [dlon] FROM  Numbered a JOIN  Numbered b ON a.[Row]+1 = b.[Row]) ,  Trig AS (SELECT  * ,  POWER(SIN(dlat/2), 2) + POWER(SIN(dlon/2), 2) * COS(lat1) * COS(lat2) AS val FROM  Paired) ,  Distance AS (SELECT  * ,  6378100 * 2 * atn2(sqrt(val),  sqrt(1-val)) AS [Distance (m)] FROM  Trig) SELECT  * ,  [Distance (m)] / NULLIF([Elapsed (s)], 0) AS [Velocity (m/s)] FROM  Distance
Equivalent_Queries:
SELECT
    *,
    [Distance (m)] / NULLIF([Elapsed (s)], 0) AS [Velocity (m/s)]
FROM (
    SELECT
        *,
        6378100 * 2 * ATN2(SQRT(val), SQRT(1 - val)) AS [Distance (m)]
    FROM (
        SELECT
            *,
            POWER(SIN(dlat / 2), 2) + POWER(SIN(dlon / 2), 2) * COS(lat1) * COS(lat2) AS val
        FROM (
            SELECT
                a.[DateTime] AS [DateTime],
                DATEDIFF(SECOND, a.[DateTime], b.[DateTime]) AS [Elapsed (s)],
                a.[LAT] AS [lat1deg],
                a.[LON] AS [lon1deg],
                b.[LAT] AS [lat2deg],
                b.[LON] AS [lon2deg],
                a.[LAT] * PI() / 180 AS [lat1],
                b.[LAT] * PI() / 180 AS [lat2],
                (a.[LAT] - b.[LAT]) * PI() / 180 AS [dlat],
                (a.[LON] - b.[LON]) * PI() / 180 AS [dlon]
            FROM (
                SELECT
                    [time] AS [DateTime],
                    [LAT],
                    [LON],
                    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY [Time] ASC) AS [Row]
                FROM (
                    SELECT DISTINCT [time], [LAT], [LON]
                    FROM [1059].[STATS_VIEW]
                ) AS UniquePos
            ) AS a
            JOIN (
                SELECT
                    [time] AS [DateTime],
                    [LAT],
                    [LON],
                    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY [Time] ASC) AS [Row]
                FROM (
                    SELECT DISTINCT [time], [LAT], [LON]
                    FROM [1059].[STATS_VIEW]
                ) AS UniquePos
            ) AS b ON a.[Row] + 1 = b.[Row]
        ) AS Paired
    ) AS Trig
) AS Distance

SQL_Statement: SELECT  NTILE(100) OVER(ORDER BY  clock asc) as progress ,  issues/ticks as issues_per_tick ,  memrefs/ticks as memrefs_per_tick ,  phantoms/ticks as phantoms_per_tick ,  streams/ticks as streams_per_tick FROM  ( SELECT  m1.source as source1,  m2.source as source2 ,  m1.clock as clock ,  (m2.clock - m1.clock) as ticks ,  (m2.issues - m1.issues)  as issues ,  (m2.memrefs - m1.memrefs)  as memrefs ,  (m2.phantoms - m1.phantoms)  as phantoms ,  (m2.streams - m1.streams)  as streams FROM  1314howe.measurement m1 ,  1314howe.measurement m2 WHERE  m2.clock > m1.clock AND  NOT EXISTS ( SELECT  clock FROM  1314howe.measurement m3 WHERE  m1.clock < m3.clock AND  m2.clock > m3.clock ) ) x ORDER BY  clock asc
Equivalent_Queries: SELECT  NTILE(100) OVER(ORDER BY  clock asc) as progress ,  issues/ticks as issues_per_tick ,  memrefs/ticks as memrefs_per_tick ,  phantoms/ticks as phantoms_per_tick ,  streams/ticks as streams_per_tick FROM  ( SELECT  m1.source as source1,  m2.source as source2 ,  m1.clock as clock ,  (m2.clock - m1.clock) as ticks ,  (m2.issues - m1.issues)  as issues ,  (m2.memrefs - m1.memrefs)  as memrefs ,  (m2.phantoms - m1.phantoms)  as phantoms ,  (m2.streams - m1.streams)  as streams FROM  1314howe.measurement m1 ,  1314howe.measurement m2 WHERE  m2.clock > m1.clock OR  NOT EXISTS ( SELECT  clock FROM  1314howe.measurement m3 WHERE  m1.clock < m3.clock AND  m2.clock > m3.clock ) ) x ORDER BY  clock asc

SQL_Statement: SELECT  maxflood.timestamp as max_flood_time ,  slackebb.timestamp as slack_ebb_time ,  maxebb.timestamp as max_ebb_time ,  slackflood.timestamp as slack_flood_time FROM  [1314howe].[Pile Point tide events labeled by tidal cycle] maxflood ,  [1314howe].[Pile Point tide events labeled by tidal cycle] slackebb ,  [1314howe].[Pile Point tide events labeled by tidal cycle] maxebb ,  [1314howe].[Pile Point tide events labeled by tidal cycle] slackflood WHERE  maxflood.current_intensity = 'Max Flood' AND  slackebb.current_intensity = '"Slack,  Ebb Begins"' AND  maxebb.current_intensity = 'Max Ebb' AND  slackflood.current_intensity = '"Slack,  Flood Begins"' AND  maxflood.tidal_cycle = slackebb.tidal_cycle AND  maxflood.tidal_cycle = maxebb.tidal_cycle AND  maxflood.tidal_cycle = slackflood.tidal_cycle
Equivalent_Queries:
SELECT 
    maxflood.timestamp as max_flood_time, 
    slackebb.timestamp as slack_ebb_time, 
    maxebb.timestamp as max_ebb_time, 
    slackflood.timestamp as slack_flood_time 
FROM 
    [1314howe].[Pile Point tide events labeled by tidal cycle] maxflood
JOIN 
    [1314howe].[Pile Point tide events labeled by tidal cycle] slackebb 
ON 
    maxflood.tidal_cycle = slackebb.tidal_cycle
    AND slackebb.current_intensity = '"Slack,  Ebb Begins"'
JOIN 
    [1314howe].[Pile Point tide events labeled by tidal cycle] maxebb 
ON 
    maxflood.tidal_cycle = maxebb.tidal_cycle
    AND maxebb.current_intensity = 'Max Ebb'
JOIN 
    [1314howe].[Pile Point tide events labeled by tidal cycle] slackflood 
ON 
    maxflood.tidal_cycle = slackflood.tidal_cycle
    AND slackflood.current_intensity = '"Slack,  Flood Begins"'
WHERE 
    maxflood.current_intensity = 'Max Flood'

SQL_Statement: WITH  Numbered AS (SELECT  [time] as [DateTime],  [LAT],  [LON],  ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY  [Time] ASC) AS [Row] FROM  [1059].[STATS_VIEW]) ,  Paired AS (SELECT  a.[DateTime] AS [DateTime] ,  DATEDIFF(second,  a.[DateTime],  b.[DateTime]) AS [Elapsed (s)] ,  a.[LAT] AS [lat1deg] ,  a.[LON] AS [lon1deg] ,  b.[LAT] AS [lat2deg] ,  b.[LON] AS [lon2deg] ,  a.[LAT] * PI() / 180 AS [lat1] ,  b.[LAT] * PI() / 180  AS [lat2] ,  (a.[LAT] - b.[LAT]) * PI() / 180 AS [dlat] ,  (a.[LON] - b.[LON]) * PI() / 180 AS [dlon] FROM  Numbered a JOIN  Numbered b ON a.[Row]+1 = b.[Row]) ,  Trig AS (SELECT  * ,  POWER(SIN(dlat/2), 2) + POWER(SIN(dlon/2), 2) * COS(lat1) * COS(lat2) AS val FROM  Paired) ,  Distance AS (SELECT  * ,  6378100 * 2 * atn2(sqrt(val),  sqrt(1-val)) AS [Distance (m)] FROM  Trig) SELECT  * ,  [Distance (m)] / NULLIF([Elapsed (s)], 0) AS [Velocity (m/s)] FROM  Distance
Equivalent_Queries:
SELECT
    *,
    6378100 * 2 * ATN2(SQRT(val), SQRT(1 - val)) AS [Distance (m)],
    6378100 * 2 * ATN2(SQRT(val), SQRT(1 - val)) / NULLIF([Elapsed (s)], 0) AS [Velocity (m/s)]
FROM (
    SELECT
        a.[DateTime],
        DATEDIFF(second, a.[DateTime], b.[DateTime]) AS [Elapsed (s)],
        a.[LAT] AS [lat1deg],
        a.[LON] AS [lon1deg],
        b.[LAT] AS [lat2deg],
        b.[LON] AS [lon2deg],
        a.[LAT] * PI() / 180 AS [lat1],
        b.[LAT] * PI() / 180 AS [lat2],
        (a.[LAT] - b.[LAT]) * PI() / 180 AS [dlat],
        (a.[LON] - b.[LON]) * PI() / 180 AS [dlon],
        POWER(SIN((a.[LAT] - b.[LAT]) * PI() / 360), 2) + 
        POWER(SIN((a.[LON] - b.[LON]) * PI() / 360), 2) * 
        COS(a.[LAT] * PI() / 180) * COS(b.[LAT] * PI() / 180) AS val
    FROM (
        SELECT 
            [time] AS [DateTime], 
            [LAT], 
            [LON], 
            ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY [time] ASC) AS [Row]
        FROM 
            [1059].[STATS_VIEW]
    ) a
    JOIN (
        SELECT 
            [time] AS [DateTime], 
            [LAT], 
            [LON], 
            ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY [time] ASC) AS [Row]
        FROM 
            [1059].[STATS_VIEW]
    ) b ON a.[Row] + 1 = b.[Row]
) AS Calculated
ORDER BY
    [DateTime];

WITH FilteredData AS (
    SELECT *
    FROM [1123].[TJGR_genomic_gene.txt]
    WHERE gID LIKE '%\_%' AND gID = 'CGI'
)
SELECT TOP 5 *, COUNT(*) OVER () AS TotalCount
FROM FilteredData

SQL_Statement: select ecp.pathway_name,  se.genus,  count(ecp.ec_number) from [ssgcid_EC_map] se join [ec_pathway.csv] ecp on ecp.ec_number = se."EC Numbers" where ecp.pathway_name <> '' group by ecp.pathway_name,  se.genus
Equivalent_Queries: select ecp.pathway_name,  se.genus,  count(ecp.ec_number) from [ssgcid_EC_map] se left join [ec_pathway.csv] ecp on ecp.ec_number = se."EC Numbers" where ecp.pathway_name <> '' group by ecp.pathway_name,  se.genus

SQL_Statement: SELECT  Distinct SightDate,  Month,  Day,  [Year] FROM  [1117].[OrcaMaster2010.csv] WHERE  [Year] BETWEEN 2006 AND  2010 AND  Pod <> 'Ts?'
Equivalent_Queries:
SELECT DISTINCT SightDate, Month, Day, [Year]
FROM (
    SELECT SightDate, Month, Day, [Year]
    FROM [1117].[OrcaMaster2010.csv]
    WHERE [Year] BETWEEN 2006 AND 2010
      AND Pod <> 'Ts?'
) AS Subquery
